--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version 5.0.2, 2026-05-07
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- UI / themes
  - **Credit:** Modernization and flattened-layout direction inspired by community PR **#73** (*Simplified Layout*, 2021) from **[@Alfa-Soft](https://github.com/Alfa-Soft)** — https://github.com/rsyslog/loganalyzer/pull/73 — reworked for the current tree rather than merged verbatim.
  - Add optional **modern** theme (`themes/modern/`): flat slate styling for `main.css` and `jquery-ui-theme.css`; neutral `about.txt` metadata (directory key **`modern`** only).
  - **Modern** theme refresh: CSS design tokens (`:root`), system font stack, lighter surfaces and shadows, clearer focus rings (`:focus-visible`), refined table and severity chip styling, and jQuery UI alignment (8px radii, shared slate/blue palette).
  - **Details popup** (grid → syslog link): dialog titlebar tied to theme; hide duplicate inner `.title` row; soften `#EventItemDetails` label cells for contrast, padding, and vertical alignment inside `.ui-dialog`.
  - **Modern** jQuery UI: `ui-state-default` surfaces (toolbars, selectmenu triggers, dialog chrome) use flat **#fff** with **no** background texture; **hover**/**focus** stay white with a stronger border, **active** stays white with the existing accent border/text; **menu** dropdown rows and **datepicker** day hovers use **#f1f5f9** so highlights remain visible on white panels; **checkbox/radio** icon boxes drop the structure inset shadow for a clean white control.
  - **Modern** theme assets: ship `themes/modern/images/` (jQuery UI **ui-icons** sprites aligned with **`jquery-ui-theme.css`**, plus **`bg_bottom.gif`** for [`include_footer.html`](src/templates/include_footer.html)) so controls and the footer bar do not 404 when the theme is active.
  - **Modern** polish (visual review): remove stray table cell / bad `</span>` closures in [`index.html`](src/templates/index.html) **SearchPanel**; flatten native + **jQuery UI** buttons (`appearance`, no `box-shadow`); white **multi-select** list surfaces; tighter cell/dialog padding; dialog **button pane** float containment + table **margin** so the last detail row is not crowded; slightly brighter **report title** links on slate headers.
  - **`ViewDefaultTheme`** in [`config.sample.php`](src/include/config.sample.php) is **`modern`** for **new** installs (installer output, Docker-generated `config.php`). Existing sites keep whatever is already in `config.php` and the user DB; PHP fallbacks for missing keys remain **`default`** so behaviour does not change until an operator updates settings.
  - Style selector list picks up new themes via existing filesystem scan.
- Templates & accessibility tidy
  - Remove deprecated **`align="left"`** from toolbar/menu `<img>` elements; align via [`css/defaults.css`](src/css/defaults.css) (`#menu` buttons, top-menu links, search form).
  - Stable hooks: **`#SearchPanel`**, **`#ProjectPanel`**, **`#PagerTop`** on main index chrome; **`#MainMenuPanel`** around the primary menu; **`#EventItemDetails`** on the detail view field table.
  - Main menu: **Help** and **KB** controls moved after authentication / user actions (before maximise).
- Robustness & i18n
  - **`DieWithErrorMsg` / `DieWithFriendlyErrorMsg`**: fix invalid extra `<tr>` in the auxiliary error table; normalise detail rows; correct friendly-error footer cell markup; trim redundant padding `<br>` in error cells ([`functions_common.php`](src/include/functions_common.php)).
  - Export placeholder copy: strip decorative **`&gt;` / `&lt;`** from **`LN_GEN_SELECTEXPORT`** in en/de/es/ja `main.php`.
- E2E / Playwright
  - **`Modern theme visual review`**: switch session style via `userchange.php`, assert theme stylesheets, capture **`modern-01`…`modern-05`** screenshots under `e2e/test-results/ci-visual/` (index grid, **details dialog**, admin index, advanced search, reports).
- Bug fixes
  - **PDO syslog summary per-host filter** (#71, PR #129): `ConsolidateDataByField` in [`logstreampdo.class.php`](src/classes/logstreampdo.class.php) now regenerates the WHERE clause for each grouped value so per-host filtering is applied correctly in syslog summary reports.
  - **DB source mapping deletion** (#61, PR #128): fix illegal-string-offset PHP warnings when deleting multiple rows from a DB source mapping; the row-index loop now operates on the correct array structure.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version 5.0.1, 2026-05-04
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Security fixes & hardening
  - CVE-2023-36306 (#105): build redirect and page URLs using `SCRIPT_NAME` instead of `PHP_SELF` to mitigate XSS via crafted paths.
  - CVE-2023-34600 (#117): remediate authenticated admin SQL injection; harden construction and escaping when SQL literals are quoted.
  - LDAP (#106): stop persisting LDAP user passwords into MySQL; bind-only semantics for directory accounts.
  - LDAP (#119 / #103): on successful LDAP login, scrub legacy salted password-hash fields previously stored locally so accounts cannot authenticate with stale hashes.
  - Frontend dependencies (#107): bump jQuery 1.12.4 → 3.7.1 and jQuery UI 1.11.1 → 1.14.1 to address upstream security defects.
- Log viewing, search filters, charts, and export UX (#88/#91 lineage)
  - Syslog PRI/level: recognise **TRACE**, apply level-based colours, optionally colour the full grid row, and tighten empty-search defaults (time window capped, hours-based `datelastx`).
  - Filters: quoted segments stay literal; support numeric ranges and reduced surprise parsing (#88).
  - Pagination: enforced upper bound on rows per page; `datelastx` clarified for backwards compatibility (#88/#91).
  - Charts: configurable default ordering for statistic charts (#88 README thread).
  - Export: plaintext / trace-aware export behaviours and README-documented workflows (#88, `4845e6f`, `a075991`).
  - Admin UI option **ViewColoredCells** toggle (#91) for styled cells in the grid.
  - Regression fixes after community UI merges: stylesheet and non-event row link styling (#88 follow-up `e966850`, `d1e501b`).
  - Supporting plumbing: coordinated updates in `functions_common.php` and `index.php` for merged behaviour (#88/#91 integration commits).
- Parsers & configuration bootstrap
  - Syslog-ng: refresh structured/exporter-oriented parsing logic (`logstreamlineparsersyslogng.class.php`, merges #96/#101).
  - Read default PHP settings safely when optional keys are absent (non-merge fix `18c40e1`) so fresh installs/upgrades skip notices.
  - PHP runtime: **`install`/runtime check requires PHP 8.1+**; PHP 8.3 compatibility tweaks (optional `track_errors`; remove legacy `html2fpdf` **`eregi`** usage).
  - bundled **html2fpdf**: tolerate PHP 8 substring/offset edge cases (#112 thread, `6600166`) atop the eregi/track_errors tidy-up above.
- Docker & Compose
  - **PHP 8.2 + MySQL 8** development stack; seeded admin and optional disk source for getting started (originally drafted for an unreleased 4.1.13 line; all shipped here under 5.0.1).
  - Compose files for **consumer** default install vs **development** bind mounts vs **Playwright/E2E** stacks; Dockerfile multi-stage bake of `src` plus optional **`/samplelogs`** fixtures (#109 baseline; follow-on PR #122/`ede5ff9`).
  - First-boot MySQL seed: optional demo disk sources via **`LOGANALYZER_SEED_SAMPLE_SOURCES`**; **`LOGANALYZER_SKIP_SEED`** for advanced automation; **`LOGANALYZER_OVERWRITE_CONFIG`** toggles regenerated `config.php` for dev ergonomics versus persisted runtime config.
  - Operator-driven disk ingestion: **`LOGANALYZER_DISK_SOURCE_PATHS`**, **`LOGANALYZER_DISK_SOURCES`** (delimiter rules in `docker/env.example`), **`LOGANALYZER_DISK_ALLOWED_EXTRA`**, **`LOGANALYZER_CONFIG_PATH`** with symlink into docroot, `docker/write-config.php` extending **`DiskAllowed`**, hardened **`InitSourceConfigs`** merging env-driven sources into DB (`ede5ff9`).
  - Rebuild/`init-env-interactive` helper scripts (.sh / .ps1 / .bat) for frictionless resets and prompting secrets (PR chain through #122).
  - Compose project invocation: **`--project-directory .`** reinforced so repo-root `.env` is honoured when using `-f docker/docker-compose.yml` (`8d9180a`, documented in handbook + PR #123); rebuild scripts propagate the same invariant.
  - Maintainership: GHCR publish workflow on semver tags (`docker-publish.yml`).
- CI, quality gates & PHP toolchain (#109/#112/#113)
  - GitHub Actions: PHP **lint matrices**, **Composer + PHPUnit**, **MkDocs Pages** builds, **Playwright E2E** against the dockerised stack, **tag-based release** tarball workflow (`.github/workflows/release-on-tag.yml`), optional failure issue bot.
  - PHPUnit: bootstrap and **fixture log cap (50MB)** under `tests/fixtures/samplelogs`.
  - Composer lock maintained for **PHP 8.1/8.2** CI (`a87ea54`); workflow reliability fixes for CI/docs publishing (`d14438e`, `99df04d`, `f472ae1`).
- Documentation site & handbook (MkDocs + GitHub Pages)
  - Material-themed handbook under `doc-site/`, legacy HTML manuals embedded and deep-linked, automated nav/hook generation for embedded manual trees (#115/#116 / `68ffeb9`, `ef472ed`).
  - GitHub Pages deployment output path corrected for Actions (`c32fb25`, #114).
  - User guide refresh plus regenerated Playwright screenshots against the live handbook (#118 / `d17cb19`).
  - Nav label quoting, legacy path cleanup when `doc/` missing, and drop obsolete `legacy-html` URL segments (#120 / `1c78744`, `73d37d9`, `2eec76c`).
